HEADWORD: articulatio
<hw>articulatio</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Latin.]</ety>
<fld>(anatomy)</fld> <def>the point of connection between two bones or
elements of a skeleton especially if the articulatio allows
motion.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> joint, articulation.</syn>⟦br⟧
